OL,3,CJersey minister to look into
OL,4,Coverturning homosexuality convictions
OL,6,FHome Affairs Minister has committed to
OL,7,Flook into overturning historical
OL,8,Fconvictions for homosexuality.
OL,10,FDeputy Mary Le Hegarat says she will
OL,11,Finvestigate whether legislation can be
OL,12,Fbrought forward so that anyone
OL,13,Fcriminalised for their sexual identity
OL,14,Fis pardoned.
OL,16,FThe minister adds: "To me, it does
OL,17,Fmake sense and it would be the right
OL,18,Fthing to do.
