OL,3,CJersey minister to look into
OL,4,Coverturning homosexuality convictions
OL,6,F"Nothing has been done so hopefully
OL,7,Fthis is the start of seeing these
OL,8,Fthings remedied."
OL,10,FSame-sex relationships were
OL,11,Fdecriminalised in Jersey in 1990 but
OL,12,FDeputy Le Hegarat says court officials
OL,13,Ffound no evidence that a conviction
OL,14,Fhas ever been quashed and it is
OL,15,Funclear whether an appeal is even
OL,16,Fpossible under the current laws.
OL,18,FShe adds she will work with members of
OL,19,Fthe LGBTQ+ community to look at the
OL,20,Flegislation.
